      <body>If you're going to link to image, use `image_tag` helper, or just mark your `&lt;img&gt;` tag has `html_safe!`

    link_to image_tag('foo.png'), '/go/to/foo'

    link_to '&lt;img src=&quot;foo.png&quot; /&gt;'.html_safe!, '/go/to/foo'

All string that isn't marked as `html_safe` will always be escaped in Rails 3.</body>
      <body-html>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;If you're going to link to image, use &lt;code&gt;image_tag&lt;/code&gt;
helper, or just mark your &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;img&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; tag has
&lt;code&gt;html_safe!&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;
&lt;code&gt;link_to image_tag('foo.png'), '/go/to/foo'

link_to '&amp;lt;img src=&quot;foo.png&quot; /&amp;gt;'.html_safe!, '/go/to/foo'&lt;/code&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All string that isn't marked as &lt;code&gt;html_safe&lt;/code&gt; will
always be escaped in Rails 3.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</body-html>
